{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019MHfFmYTNSfEF6FcT4YDUW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# allocate\n2\t\n3\t`allocate.split_amount(total, parts)` splits a whole number `total` into `parts`\n4\tinteger shares.\n5\t\n6\tContract:\n7\t\n8\t- `parts` is an integer >= 1 and `total` is an integer >= 0.\n9\t- Return a list of exactly `parts` non-negative integers whose sum is exactly `total`.\n10\t- The shares are as equal as possible: every share is either `total // parts` or one\n11\t  greater, and the `total % parts` extra units go to the earliest shares, so the list\n12\t  comes out non-increasing.\n13\t\n14\tExamples:\n15\t\n16\t    split_amount(100, 3) -> [34, 33, 33]\n17\t    split_amount(90, 3)  -> [30, 30, 30]\n18\t    split_amount(7, 2)   -> [4, 3]\n19\t\n20\tRun the tests with:\n21\t\n22\t    python -m unittest discover -s tests -t .\n23\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89a77418-5803-420b-93c0-b19d1382ee86","uuid":"f922b624-325d-44a5-b453-d2460bd522b9","timestamp":"2026-07-24T02:10:55.794Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"README.md","content":"# allocate\n\n`allocate.split_amount(total, parts)` splits a whole number `total` into `parts`\ninteger shares.\n\nContract:\n\n- `parts` is an integer >= 1 and `total` is an integer >= 0.\n- Return a list of exactly `parts` non-negative integers whose sum is exactly `total`.\n- The shares are as equal as possible: every share is either `total // parts` or one\n  greater, and the `total % parts` extra units go to the earliest shares, so the list\n  comes out non-increasing.\n\nExamples:\n\n    split_amount(100, 3) -> [34, 33, 33]\n    split_amount(90, 3)  -> [30, 30, 30]\n    split_amount(7, 2)   -> [4, 3]\n\nRun the tests with:\n\n    python -m unittest discover -s tests -t .\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
